Evaluate the transcribed content against the original audio. Only detect wrong words, hallucinations (invented speech not in audio), and missing content that exists in the audio.

Do not evaluate grammar, formatting, or transcription style - only factual alignment with what was actually spoken. Only flag issues if transcription contradicts, adds to, or omits speech from the audio.

Rate overall score (how well transcription matches audio) on a 0.0 to 1.0 scale.
Rate clarity (audio quality and intelligibility) on a 0.0 to 1.0 scale.

